    "created_at": "2018-06-15T08:15:02Z",
    "updated_at": "2018-06-15T08:15:02Z",
    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "@alimanfoo I'm not sure it applies directly to your problem, but to get the equivalent of vmin/vmax for the colormap, I do the following:\r\n```python\r\n# given df, cmap, vmin, vmax:\r\ndf_data = df.copy()\r\ndf = df.clip(vmin, vmax)\r\ndf = df.style.background_gradient(cmap=cmap)\r\ndf.data = df_data\r\n```"
